At least seven people were killed and 70 injured  when a bus plunged into a gorge in the northern Himalayan state of Himachal  Pradesh on Monday, the Press Trust of India said.
The bus rolled down a 45 metre (150 foot) ravine near Bilaspur town, the  news agency said. The injured included several children on their way to school.
The state government has announced a payment of 25,000 rupees (833  dollars) to the familes of the dead.
